        "Statement I is false but Statement II is true."
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "<p>Statement - I: Rate of $$\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 2 \\propto[\\mathrm{R}-\\mathrm{X}]\\left[\\mathrm{Nu}^{-}\\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 2$$ reaction is favoured by high concentration of nucleophile $$(\\mathrm{Nu}^{-})$$ & less crowding in the substrate molecule.</p>\n<p>Statement - II: Solvolysis follows $$\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 1$$ path.</p>\n<p>Both are correct Statements.</p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Haloalkanes and Haloarenes"
